                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d508">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">123 Biddle, Anthony J. D./236: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Bordeaux</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-24T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 24, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>34. Your 68, June 22, 11 a.m. Your designation as representative near the French
                    Government was special and for the emergency period during the time the French
                    Government was separated from the capital by military necessity. The President
                    now desires that you proceed to Bilbao or some other point in Spain until such
                    time as you may find it possible to arrange safe transportation to England in
                    order to resume your post near the Polish Government.</p>
                <p>We will telegraph later instructions regarding the staff.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
